5 Subject: Agriculture; procurement; local food; State agencies
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to provide that it
7 is the State policy to encourage the procurement of local foods by State
8 institutions and State universities and colleges to increase the viability of
9 Vermont farms and food businesses. The bill would provide that a State
10 institution or a State university or college purchasing food shall provide a
11 preference to local foods when local foods are comparable in costs to foods
12 that have not been grown or produced in the State. The bill would require a
13 person responsible for procuring food or other items on behalf of a State
14 institution or a State university or college to purchase local foods unless the
15 price of local goods exceeds by more than 10 percent the price of food or other
16 agricultural products grown or produced that were not grown or produced
17 within Vermont.
