1 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
2 Sec. 1. FINDINGS
3 The General Assembly finds that:
4 (1) Vermont recognizes the importance of local production and supply
5 as a means to empower communities, strengthen local economies, and ensure
6 access to healthy, locally produced foods;
7 (2) institutional purchasing from Vermont farms can significantly
8 bolster the State’s agricultural sector, support sustainable farming practices,
9 and promote economic resilience; and
10 (3) the State should support Vermont farms and the farming economy by
11 giving preference to local foods in the purchasing by State agencies, State
12 universities, and State colleges.
13 Sec. 2. 29 V.S.A. chapter 49, subchapter 3 is added to read:
14 Subchapter 3. State Purchasing of Food
15 § 941. DEFINITIONS
16 As used in this subchapter:
17 (1) “Local food” has the same meaning as “local,” “local to Vermont,”
18 and “locally grown or made in Vermont” as in 9 V.S.A. § 2465a.
19 (2) “State agency” means any Executive Branch agency, department, or
20 entity created by Title 3 of the Vermont Statutes Annotated and any board,
