1 commission, council, or similar entity attached to an Executive Branch agency,
2 department, or entity.
3 (3) “State universities and colleges” means the University of Vermont
4 and the Vermont State Colleges.
5 (4) “State institution” means any State agency, any office of the State
6 judiciary, and any office of the General Assembly.
7 § 942. STATE POLICY
8 It is the policy of the State to encourage the procurement of local foods by
9 State institutions and State universities and colleges to increase the viability of
10 Vermont farms and food businesses, thus making a positive contribution to the
11 State’s economy and enhancing food self-sufficiency for Vermont.
12 § 943. PREFERENCE FOR LOCAL FOOD
13 (a) Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, and to the extent permitted by
14 federal law, a State institution or a State university or college purchasing food
15 shall provide a preference to local foods when local foods are comparable in
16 costs to foods that have not been grown or produced in the State.
17 (b) The person responsible for procuring food or other items on behalf of a
18 State institution or a State university or college shall purchase local foods
19 unless the price of local goods exceeds by more than 10 percent the price of
20 food or other agricultural products grown or produced that were not grown or
21 produced within Vermont.
